1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
In 2021, DeFi option vaults like Ribbon and Friktion did billions in volume.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
A year later, they were dead.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
They sold options too cheap, leaking value to market makers.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
And unhedged, one crash wiped out the LPs.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Picking up pennies in front of a steamroller.

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I'm rebuilding structured vaults on Sui, with both of those problems fixed.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
This is Squall.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Squall is a structured-yield vault on Sui, and it changes the model in two ways.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Instead of cheap auctions, it provides liquidity on DeepBook Predict's vol-priced order book,

10
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
earning the spread from real trading flow.

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
And it's hedged by design, so a crash can't wipe it out.

12
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Everything you're about to see, you can verify yourself.

13
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Let me walk you through it, as one dive into the Sui ocean.

14
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,000
We start at the surface. You deposit USDC,

15
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
and the vault mints you a share token in return.

16
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,000
It's a standard ERC-4626 vault, the proven yield-vault standard, now in Move on Sui.

17
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Mint shares, mark net asset value, withdraw anytime.

18
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:28,000
No options knowledge, no lockups. Everything interesting happens below the surface.

19
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Before deploying a dollar, the vault asks: what is the fair price of risk right now?

20
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Our keeper, a small off-chain service, reads DeepBook's live volatility surface,

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:47,000
and publishes it on-chain as the Vol Index, the first on-chain volatility index on Sui.

22
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:52,000
It's smoothed, so it stays stable, not noisy.

23
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:58,000
That index is the price tag on every position the vault takes.

24
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:04,000
So the vault never guesses. It prices risk off a live, on-chain benchmark.

25
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:10,000
That's the brain. Now we go deeper.

26
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:16,000
We dive into the depths, DeepBook Predict, our primary sponsor.

27
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,000
This is where Squall earns.

28
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:27,000
On the right, OracleSVI is the live volatility surface that prices every trade.

29
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:34,000
In the middle is the vol-priced order book, where traders pay the spread,

30
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,000
real, recurring flow, not a cheap weekly auction.

31
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:45,000
So the vault calls supply, hands over USDC, and becomes the house,

32
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:50,000
holding a PLP position that backs the book.

33
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:56,000
As traders pay the spread, that position accrues value, marked to NAV each epoch.

34
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:01,000
And a tail hedge caps the crash that killed the old vaults.

35
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Squall isn't gambling. It's the house.

36
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Finally we reach the seabed, Walrus, our second sponsor.

37
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
This is where Squall earns trust.

38
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Every epoch, the vault writes a snapshot to Walrus and gets back a blobId.

39
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:28,000
That blobId is a content hash, so the snapshot can never be quietly changed.

40
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Each snapshot also embeds the previous one's id, forming a hash-chain you can't reorder or alter.

41
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:44,000
And the keeper anchors each one on Sui, in a ProofLog recording the NAV and blobId.

42
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:51,000
So the history is complete and tamper-proof: the on-chain log is the index.

43
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:58,000
To verify, anyone re-fetches the blob and checks it against the on-chain anchor.

44
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Our Proof tab does exactly that, live. Trust by proof, not by promise.

45
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:10,000
And this isn't a mockup. Here's Squall, live on Sui testnet.

46
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,000
I connect my wallet and deposit a hundred test USDC.

47
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:21,000
I approve, and I receive my vault shares, vSTRATA.

48
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
The toast gives me a transaction link. Let's follow it to Suiscan.

49
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Real testnet: a hundred USDC in, vault shares out, and the object is the Squall Vault.

50
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Here's our strategy on-chain, with real supply and withdraw calls into DeepBook Predict.

51
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Deposit, allocate, harvest, redeem, all verified on-chain.

52
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:51,000
This gauge is our on-chain Vol Index, reading live.

53
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Here's the same VolIndex object on Suiscan, with the keeper's updates.

54
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Now the proof. These are our NAV attestations.

55
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:08,000
I click verify, and the app re-fetches the blob from Walrus and confirms it.

56
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:15,000
And here's that exact blob on Walruscan, by its content ID, immutable and public.

57
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Anyone can check it. Nothing here is taken on faith.

58
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:26,000
And I can withdraw anytime, burn the shares, USDC back.

59
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Deposit at the surface. Price risk off the first on-chain vol index on Sui.

60
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Earn the spread as the house on DeepBook. Prove every number on Walrus.

61
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:48,000
That's Squall. Structured yield you don't have to trust. You can verify it.

62
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Live on Sui testnet now.
